Hi Sidharth,

Thank you for your email.  Can I ask that you please check and ensure that "DPI Bypass" is enabled for the affected machine and let me know please?  Enabling this in our remote session yesterday together with adding the domains to the whitelist solved the issue.  Also please don't forget to again add the DPI whitelist dictionaries each time when you are modifying the Content Aware Policy.





Kind regards

Hi Andre,

We have created tickets for each issue mentioned below by Sai, I will mention the same along with the summary for your perusal.


  1.  00428409 - Netwrix EPP blocking a tool from a URL, was resolved briefly after a session with you but the issue persisted and is still causing problems.
  2.  00425192 - File uploads on whatsapp application are blocked but copy pasting images via PrntScr or capturing screenshot via snippet tool is getting uploaded on the whatsapp application.
  3.  00421220 - A general issue affecting the policies, where the policies are not getting enforced intermittently and user ends up exploiting this loophole thereby rendering the DLP policies configured in EPP useless. This issue has been observed mainly across CAP policies.
  4.  Skype as an application is getting blocked (ticket not yet raised) - Customer has specific policies for specific groups. One of the groups required skype as an application to be blocked so we have applied policy to block skype on that group. This also somehow affected skype application to get blocked in another group in which the skype application is required to be run. Skype is not defined in the application denylist in that policy, yet it is blocked by EPP. Removing the machine from that policy enables skype application to run without any issues.


[signature_2251198256]

We have created tickets for each issue mentioned below by Sai, I will mention the same along with the summary for your perusal.



  1.  00428409 – Netwrix EPP blocking a tool from a URL, was resolved briefly after a session with you but the issue persisted and is still causing problems.
  2.  00425192 – File uploads on whatsapp application are blocked but copy pasting images via PrntScr or capturing screenshot via snippet tool is getting uploaded on the whatsapp application.
  3.  00421220 – A general issue affecting the policies, where the policies are not getting enforced intermittently and user ends up exploiting this loophole thereby rendering the DLP policies configured in EPP useless. This issue has been observed mainly across CAP policies.
  4.  Skype as an application is getting blocked (ticket not yet raised) – Customer has specific policies for specific groups. One of the groups required skype as an application to be blocked so we have applied policy to block skype on that group. This also somehow affected skype application to get blocked in another group in which the skype application is required to be run. Skype is not defined in the application denylist in that policy, yet it is blocked by EPP. Removing the machine from that policy enables skype application to run without any issues.

Hi Andre, 

  

We have created tickets for each issue mentioned below by Sai, I will mention the same along with the summary for your perusal. 

  


	00428409 – Netwrix EPP blocking a tool from a URL, was resolved briefly after a session with you but the issue persisted and is still causing problems. 
	00425192 – File uploads on whatsapp application are blocked but copy pasting images via PrntScr or capturing screenshot via snippet tool is getting uploaded on the whatsapp application. 
	00421220 – A general issue affecting the policies, where the policies are not getting enforced intermittently and user ends up exploiting this loophole thereby rendering the DLP policies configured in EPP useless. This issue has been observed mainly across CAP policies. 
	Skype as an application is getting blocked (ticket not yet raised) – Customer has specific policies for specific groups. One of the groups required skype as an application to be blocked so we have applied policy to block skype on that group. This also somehow affected skype application to get blocked in another group in which the skype application is required to be run. Skype is not defined in the application denylist in that policy, yet it is blocked by EPP. Removing the machine from that policy enables skype application to run without any issues.

Hi Andre, 

  

We have created tickets for each issue mentioned below by Sai, I will mention the same along with the summary for your perusal. 

  


	00428409 – Netwrix EPP blocking a tool from a URL, was resolved briefly after a session with you but the issue persisted and is still causing problems. 
	00425192 – File uploads on whatsapp application are blocked but copy pasting images via PrntScr or capturing screenshot via snippet tool is getting uploaded on the whatsapp application. 
	00421220 – A general issue affecting the policies, where the policies are not getting enforced intermittently and user ends up exploiting this loophole thereby rendering the DLP policies configured in EPP useless. This issue has been observed mainly across CAP policies. 
	Skype as an application is getting blocked (ticket not yet raised) – Customer has specific policies for specific groups. One of the groups required skype as an application to be blocked so we have applied policy to block skype on that group. This also somehow affected skype application to get blocked in another group in which the skype application is required to be run. Skype is not defined in the application denylist in that policy, yet it is blocked by EPP. Removing the machine from that policy enables skype application to run without any issues.
